article.headline: North Dakota State 91, Idaho 76
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho (AP) -- Brett Winkelman led North Dakota State with 32 points Friday night as the Bison defeated Idaho 91-76 in the nonconference season opener for both teams. After jumping out to a 6-0 lead, the Vandals faded and fell behind North Dakota State by as many as eight points several times in the first half. Idaho then put together a run led by senior post Desmond Nwoke, who scored eight consecutive points. Trevor Morris continued to inch Idaho closer when he hit a 3-pointer with 2:05 left in the half to bring Idaho within five, 36-31. Another 9-3 Idaho run, punctuated by a 3-pointer from Miles Webb, left the game tied at 40 at halftime. The Bison, who were a dismal 2-11 on the road last season, led by as many as 19 points in the second half. North Dakota State lit up the scoreboard, hitting 19-for-28 from the floor in the second half, while connecting on 10-of-13 free throws. North Dakota State held a slim 55-52 lead with 12:57 left to play. But then the Bison went on a 23-8 run that ended the Vandals' hopes. Andre Smith added 20 points for North Dakota State, while Ben Woodside had 18 and Mike Nelson scored 13. The Vandals were led by Mario Mackey's 21 points. Clyde Johnson added 14 and Webb scored 12.
